-- North Korea to Allow Businessmen From South Back Into Gaeseong
-- B y   S a n g w o n   Y o o n
-- 2013-07-03T12:12:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-03/north-korea-to-allow-businessmen-from-south-back-into-gaeseong.html
 North Korean officials contacted
South Korean counterparts today to announce they will allow
South Korean businessmen back into the jointly-run
factory park in the North Korean border city of Gaeseong, South
Korea’s Unification Ministry says in e-mailed statement.
*NOTE: Gaeseong industrial zone has been shut since the North
withdrew its workers in April
* North Korea willing to let South Korean businessmen visit
Gaeseong and discuss how to deal with remaining equipment amid
concerns for possible flooding ahead of summer monsoon season
start: S. Korea
* North Korea said it is willing to also let South Korean
officials responsible for handling Gaeseong affairs to discuss
“necessary affairs”: S. Korea
* North Korea pledged cooperation if S. Koreans give a date for
visit: S. Korea  To contact the reporter on this story:
